thane as a stable clathrate-hydrate in Titan's interior for later release to the atmosphere is quite plausible. There is also some likelihood that the production of methane on Titan by serpentinization is a gradual and continuous on-going process. {\textcopyright} 2006 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.},
